Modifications relative to upstream TrackMate
---------------------------------------------

The following files in trackmate_py/ are Python translations of the
named upstream Java classes. They were created by Digin Dominic on
2026-04-07.

  trackmate_py/__init__.py             (package re-exports)
  trackmate_py/detection_utils.py      ← fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.DetectionUtils
                                          + MedianFilter2D
                                          + imglib2 LocalExtrema / SubpixelLocalization
  trackmate_py/dog_detector.py         ← fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.DogDetector
  trackmate_py/log_detector.py         ← fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.LogDetector
  trackmate_py/hessian_detector.py     ← fiji.plugin.trackmate.detection.HessianDetector
                                          + imglib2 HessianMatrix / PartialDerivative
  trackmate_py/minesjtk_fft.py         ← edu.mines.jtk.dsp.{Pfacc, FftReal, FftComplex}
                                          + net.imglib2.algorithm.fft2.FFT*

The translations were verified bit-for-bit against the upstream Java
pipeline on a representative microscopy tile
(SD0311_A_FPS1_VGATSV2A_R_270125_QWC_VGAT_CY5_XY00660.tif): 33/33 TSV
columns matched exactly across the DoG, LoG, and Hessian detectors
(19499 spots on Hessian, 10191 on DoG, 9808 on LoG).

The wrapper scripts and numba accelerators are original work by Digin
Dominic, also released under GPL v3 because they form a combined work
with the GPL-licensed translations.

  run_trackmate_python_headless.py     (pure-Python entry point — no JVM)
  run_trackmate_fiji_headless.py       (legacy PyImageJ entry point — optional)
  _metric_helpers_numba.py             (numba accelerators for per-spot metrics)


